frameDefinitions: A physical object, the Artifact, is produced by a Creator to stimulate the perceptions, emotions, or cognition of an audience.
Criteria exist that identify a particular Subset of a Group of things into members and non-members.
A Speaker addresses an Audience on a particular Topic.
A Cognizer has a Judgment of an Evaluee, expressing how high or low their regard for the Evaluee is.
A Wearer wears accessories, which are made of  some Material and may have a Style.
An Artifact is deliberately made or modified by an intelligent entity to be put to a certain kind of Use.
frameExamples: Sir Denis Mahon is the owner of the most important private collection of Italian Baroque <t><fex name='Artifact'>paintings</fex></t>.
Urban areas have> a higher teen suicide <t><fex name='Ratio'>rate</fex></t> than rural areas.
McNamara <t>addressed</t> congress on the state of affairs of the Department of Defense.
What do you <t>think</t> of him as a linguist?
She wore a black velvet <t>hat</t> on her head.
There are reports that Kim Il Sung asked China to share its nuclear weapons <t>technology</t>.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the entity or substance that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Artifact</fen> is presently located.
A representation of the conditions upon which membership to a <fen>Subset</fen> of a <fen>Group</fen> is determined.
The members of a <fen>Group</fen> that fulfill particular <fen>Criteria</fen> to belong to a <fen>Subset</fen> of the <fen>Group</fen>.
The numerical representation of the size of the <fen>Subset</fen> relative to the size of the <fen>Group</fen>.
The person or persons to whom the <fen>Speaker</fen> delivers their text.
The person who orally delivers a text about a <fen>Topic</fen> to a passive <fen>Audience</fen>.
What the text that the <fen>Speaker</fen> produces is about.
The <fen>Time</fen> describes when the speaking occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> describes the location where the speaking occurs.
The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the one that makes a <fen>Judgment</fen>. This role is typically expressed as the External Argument (or in a <ment>by</ment>-PP in passives).
<fen>Evaluee</fen> is the person or thing that a judgment is made with respect to. With verbs this role is typically expressed as Object:
A description (from the point of view of the <fen>Cognizer</fen>) of the position of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> on a scale of approval.

This role identifies the entity or substance that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>. This can refer to physical artifacts, like a mug or computer monitor, or a digital artifact, such as a website or document.
